<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES70-5 - REASSEMBLY - SHIFT
        TOWER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301166">Figure 66</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301166" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301166" filename="../figg13/G1301166.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 66. Shift Tower - Exploded View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HANDLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SPRING RETAINER LOCK PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>6. BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. ROCK SHAFT PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>8. GASKET</callout1>
                <callout1>9. LEVER HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>10. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>11. LEVER COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>12. SPRING RETAINER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the lever housing on edge in a vise.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hold the shift lever so that the lever cross hole aligns with the rock shaft cross hole in
                the lever housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the rock shaft pin through the holes in the lever housing and shift lever.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the rock shaft snap ring to the groove of the lever housing, locking the rock shaft
                in place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next, place a new, lightly greased seal on the lever housing. Grease the inner wall of the
                cup, and slide it over the lever into position on the dome.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the spring, spring retainer, and lever cover over the shift lever. Depress the
                spring retainer and insert the spring retainer lock pin through the hole in the lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the shift lever handle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shift lever and lever housing assembly on the shifter housing with a gasket,
                noting that the finger enters the neutral position notches.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the assembly with bolts and lockwashers. Tighten to 25 to 41 ft-lbs. (34-56 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
